{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh cold water into it. Add gelatine leaves to bowl with water. Leave to soak until swelled and softened (approx. 7-10 minutes).","Place cream and honey into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>4 min\/60°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg yolks and tahini into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer into a separate bowl and set aside.","Place reserved cream mixture back into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>, slowly adding tahini mixture through hole in mixing bowl lid, then cook <nobr>4 min\/80°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Squeeze gelatine leaves to remove excess water, then add leaves to mixing bowl and mix <nobr>4 min\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Discard soaking water. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Pass tahini cream mixture through a fine mesh sieve or nut milk bag into a bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to set for a minimum of 4 hours. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place tahini cream into mixing bowl and blend <nobr>20 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and repeat blending <nobr>20 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr> or until smooth.","Divide tahini cream between 4 serving bowls and top with blackberries, edible flowers and herbs just before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g cold water","3 titanium strength gelatine leaves","500 g pouring (whipping) cream","100 g honey","6 egg yolks","50 g tahini","200 g fresh blackberries, to serve (see Tips)","edible flowers (e.g.unsprayed pansies and orange blossoms) or herbs (e.g. baby mint leaves), to serve (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r103988","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-8VXrBG6y3Pk\/XZWfIuWLBAI\/AAAAAAAAe_Y\/1TCZ9H5TEVcfqkwlQYfeik2tsovRrHYwgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_p0K0MtZiRAFOXZzJ.png","title":"Tahini cream with blackberries (Raymond Capaldi)","publishedAt":"2016-12-28T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.157 g","fat":"58.798 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.043 g","calories":"2823 kJ \/ 672 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, bowl, nut bag or fine mesh sieve, plastic wrap, 4 serving bowls, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If fresh blackberries are unavailable, use 200 g frozen blackberries, thawed and drained on paper towel to remove excess moisture.","Edible flowers are a wonderful addition to both sweet and savoury dishes. It is best to grow your own or purchase from a reputable organic supplier so you can avoid herbicides or pesticides.","Reserve egg whites and use in omelettes, pavlova or mousses."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","4h 30m","4 portions"]}